Text:
@darkpiro: I see you used google, but still got it wrong. 

A TS (telesync) is a camcorder that syncs its framerate to the screen, resulting in a "cam" video w/o any flicker. At least, that's what it used to mean, although there's so much crap online these days that you can probably find any definition you want on google.

(Hence, if this is the same cam video, it is probably not a ts--not if there's any flicker.)
